<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-522-711  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 522 711.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Oct 22 1990 v24 n43 p23(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Get ready for staffing squeeze. (guidelines for attracting goodinformation systems people)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Peterson, Duwayne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>In the 1990s, information systems (IS) organizations will findthemselves facing increasing pressure to retain enough qualifiedpersonnel.andP;  While many corporations are reducing their work forcesto save money, the computer systems developed in the 1970s and1980s are best maintained by the employees who set them up.andP;  Newtechnologies, the need to re-engineer old systems, and stepped-upcompetition from outsourcing companies and systems integrators areall increasing demand for skilled IS people.andP;  Companies must takesteps to assure their attractiveness.andP;  Open communication withmanagement, giving responsibilities and powers to IS people, jobsecurity, praise, plus a good company reputation, all help attractgood IS people.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MISGuidelinesManagement StyleRecruitmentEDP Personnel.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>